1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA §6171, sub-§6 is enacted to read:
3 6. Emergency rules to limit taking of marine organisms. Notwithstanding
4 subsections 3 and 5, the commissioner may adopt routine technical rules as emergency
5 rules under Title 5, section 8054 that limit the taking of marine organisms by method or
6 location to protect marine mammals listed under section 6975 when the commissioner
7 determines that immediate action is necessary to mitigate circumstances posing an
8 exceptionally high level of risk to those mammals.
9 Sec. 2. Report on use of emergency rule-making authority. The Department
10 of Marine Resources shall, no later than December 1, 2027, submit a report to the joint
11 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over marine resources matters
12 regarding any uses of the emergency rule-making authority established in the Maine
13 Revised Statutes, Title 12, section 6171, subsection 6. The report must include any findings
14 and recommendations derived from the department's experience in using that authority.
15 The joint standing committee may report out a bill based on the report to the Second
16 Regular Session of the 133rd Legislature.
17 SUMMARY
